My biggest concern is that many people who have been fighting this battle for going on a decade will become the very thing they hate by not knowing when they've won and will become the extremist side of the same coin as current radical progressives.  Just like many progressives, I feel like "fighting woke" (which was a valiant battle) has become, to some, a large part of their identity, and they'll struggle to adapt. 

Think about it....for the most part, liberals and progressives got what they wanted. Racism was at all time lows, gay marriage was legalized and no longer stigmatized....hell, they even got most people to agree to call people by fake pronouns, but they just couldn't stop once they got everything they'd been fighting for.  That lead to modern progressives trying to do the ridiculous like going after kids and putting men in women's sports.  THOSE are the things that led to their downfall, not the issues they were originally fighting for.  We can't make the same mistake else the pendulum will swing back.

